{giam_service_account}
resources: listing and deletion across roles.

[[rbtgog_access]]
//axvo_group axd_tabtarget
{rbtgog_access}::
Diagnostic operations verifying
{rbtr_role}
authentication and registry access via OAuth and JWT probes.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_image_muster}

NOTE: This operation produces a flat catalog of identifiers under one of the three GAR domains
(hallmarks, reliquaries, enshrinements)
in
{rbtgi_repository}
via the GAR REST API implemented by
{gar_service}.
Identifiers only — no per-member presence detail (use {rbtgo_image_rekon} for that), and no health classification (use {rbtgo_hallmark_tally} for that).

The
{rbtr_director}
musters over three domains, each backed by a distinct procedure:

* `rbfl_muster_hallmarks` — every hallmark identifier under the `hallmarks/` root
* `rbfl_muster_reliquaries` — every reliquary stamp under the `reliquaries/` root
* `rbfl_muster_enshrinements` — every enshrined base anchor under the `enshrines/` root

Muster vs. {rbtgo_hallmark_tally}: muster is a {rbtr_director}-tier flat-list operation across all three domains; tally is a {rbtr_retriever}-tier hallmarks-only operation that classifies each entry by basename completeness and vouch status.
The two roles compose without overlap.

== Hallmarks Muster

The
{rbtr_director}
musters hallmark identifiers:

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Packages Under Hallmarks Root*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARKS_ROOT»` from `RBGL_HALLMARKS_ROOT` (kindled as `RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX` + `hallmarks`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REPO_BASE»` as the GAR REST API repository base (`projects/«PROJECT»/locations/«REGION»/repositories/«REPOSITORY»`)
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages?pageSize=1000`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Extract `.packages[].name`, strip the resource prefix, URL-decode `%2F` back to `/`, and retain only entries beginning with `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»/`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARK_ROWS»` as `«HALLMARK» «BASENAME»` pairs derived from those entries (a 2-deep enumeration shared with {rbtgo_image_rekon})

//axhos_step
. *Project to Unique Identifiers*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARKS»` as the ordered set of distinct hallmark identifiers from the first column of `«HALLMARK_ROWS»`

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_ark}
. *Display Results*:
.. If `«HALLMARKS»` is empty:
... {rbbc_show}
"No hallmarks found under «HALLMARKS_ROOT»/"
... return success with count `0`
.. Otherwise:
... {rbbc_show}
table header `HALLMARK`
... For each `«HALLMARK»` in `«HALLMARKS»`:
.... {rbbc_show}
`«HALLMARK»`
... {rbbc_show}
"Total hallmarks: «COUNT»"

== Reliquaries Muster

The
{rbtr_director}
musters reliquary stamps:

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Packages Under Reliquaries Root*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RELIQUARIES_ROOT»` from `RBGL_RELIQUARIES_ROOT` (kindled as `RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX` + `reliquaries`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REPO_BASE»` as the GAR REST API repository base
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages?pageSize=1000`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Extract `.packages[].name`, strip the resource prefix, URL-decode `%2F` back to `/`, and retain only entries beginning with `«RELIQUARIES_ROOT»/`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RELIQUARY_ROWS»` as `«STAMP» «TOOL»` pairs derived from those entries (a 2-deep enumeration shared with {rbtgo_image_rekon})

//axhos_step
. *Project to Unique Stamps*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«STAMPS»` as the ordered set of distinct reliquary stamps from the first column of `«RELIQUARY_ROWS»`

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbst_reliquary_stamp}
. *Display Results*:
.. If `«STAMPS»` is empty:
... {rbbc_show}
"No reliquaries found under «RELIQUARIES_ROOT»/"
... return success with count `0`
.. Otherwise:
... {rbbc_show}
table header `RELIQUARY-STAMP`
... For each `«STAMP»` in `«STAMPS»`:
.... {rbbc_show}
`«STAMP»`
... {rbbc_show}
"Total reliquaries: «COUNT»"

== Enshrinements Muster

The
{rbtr_director}
musters enshrined base anchors:

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Anchors Under Enshrines Root*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ENSHRINES_ROOT»` from `RBGL_ENSHRINES_ROOT` (kindled as `RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX` + `enshrines`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REPO_BASE»` as the GAR REST API repository base
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages?pageSize=1000`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Extract `.packages[].name`, strip the resource prefix, URL-decode `%2F` back to `/`, and retain only entries beginning with `«ENSHRINES_ROOT»/`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ANCHORS»` as the list of anchor segments (1-deep enumeration — enshrines are flat, one image per anchor; see helper `zrbfc_list_anchors_capture`)

//axhoot_typed_output
